	<td width="100%" colspan="2" align="center" valign="middle" background="themes/BlueMetal/forums/images/cellpic1.gif"><a href="modules.php?name=ForumNews&news_id=1" border="0"><strong>Announcements</a>: <span class="block-title">Chronicles theme going live for entire board...</span></strong></td>
        </tr>
<tr>
<td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td rowspan="5" valign="left" align="center" width="13%"><a href="modules.php?name=ForumNews&news_id=1" border="0"><img src="images/topics/Announce.jpg" border="0" alt="Announcements" title="Announcements" /></a></td>
		<td valign="top" width="87%"><b>Posted by </b><a href="modules.php?name=Forums&file=profile&mode=viewprofile&u=2"><b>Ailuvan</b></a> on Tue Sep 30, 2003 8:15 am</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign="bottom">Later today, I am installing the Chronicles theme, for the Board and Forum, as the only choice, and deleting all fo the other themes....
<br />

<br />
I would love to leave the other themes up, but administratively, it's a nightmare, since some of the modules I have to install require modifications to the theme files, and I just can't edit every theme in use to customize them, since it's actually a matter of figuring out what is changing, and adapting the changes to the themes not mentioned in the install directions.
<br />

<br />
The new theme is nice, though, if you're not using it, and Lorinthian came up with a nice banner at the top of the page.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td VALIGN="top"><b><hr></b></td>
