	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign="bottom">Yes, the new incarnation of my mailer script works. And even better, You Control Your Own Mail Addresses! <img src="modules/Forums/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If you go to the <a href="http://www.intrinsicsense.net/modules.php?name=Your_Account" target="_blank" class="postlink">Your Account</a> module, and then into <span style="font-weight: bold">Your Info</span>, add a line to your <span style="font-weight: bold">Extra Info</span> that looks like this:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">mailto&#58;Ailuvan</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That's it, all on one line, no spaces, nothing fancy.
<br />

<br />
All mail to a addresses @members.intrinsicsense.net is passed through a filter that checks to see if someone on the board "claims" that address.  So, for example, Bough might have, in his <span style="font-weight: bold">Extra Info</span>:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">mailto&#58;Bough
<br />
mailto&#58;Gaturz
<br />
mailto&#58;Forje</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
All mail matched to a user in this manner is automatically forwarded to the <span style="font-weight: bold">Real Email Address</span> shown in the <span style="font-weight: bold">Your Info</span> page.  Int his case, mail to any of <a href="mailto:Bough@members.intrinsicsense.net">Bough@members.intrinsicsense.net</a>, <a href="mailto:Gaturz@members.intrinsicsense.net">Gaturz@members.intrinsicsense.net</a>, or <a href="mailto:Forje@members.intrinsicsense.net">Forje@members.intrinsicsense.net</a>, would all be sent to Bough's real email address, transparently to whoever is sending the mail.
<br />

<br />
Any questions, post below, or send me a email to <a href="mailto:ailuvan@intrinsicsense.net">ailuvan@intrinsicsense.net</a> (or <a href="mailto:ailuvan@members.intrinsicsense.net">ailuvan@members.intrinsicsense.net</a> <img src="modules/Forums/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> )</td>
