	<tr>
		<td valign="bottom">This is the first post for the new Portal.
<br />

<br />
If you are a forum moderator, you have some new options when you make a post.  The first is a dropdown box, under the Subject, labeled "Select News Category".  This should be OoS, OoC, Raids, whichever is appropriate to the area where you're making the post.  The second is the "Announcement" selector down below the message, in the Options section, along with "Normal" and "Sticky".
<br />

<br />
When Announcement is set below, and any category other than "Regular Post" is set above, this post will appear in the news section of the soon-to-be front page.
<br />

<br />
It's not too difficult.  I do need to make sure the appropriate people have moderator access to the furms then should, so you all need to check that, as well.  If you can moderate a forum, when you're looking at the list of topics in that forum, at the bottom of the screen in the list of things that you can do in that forum ("You can read", "You can reply", etc) should be a "You can Moderate this forum" link.  If you don't have that, you're not a moderator, and you need to send me a message.</td>
